<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-01T20:00:00-05:00" n="896" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                            <p>On September 6, 1953, Prime Minister Ghazi resigned and Prince
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DSMK1">Mohammed Daud</persName> formed a
                                new government in which the former Ambassador to the United States,
                                    <persName corresp="#p_NSM1">Mohammed Naim</persName>, became the
                                Foreign Minister.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>